model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__order_.description: Represents the shipping details that the customer chose for their order.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

carrier_identifier.name: carrier_identifier
carrier_identifier.description: A reference to the carrier service that provided the rate. Present when the rate was computed by a third-party carrier service.

code.name: code
code.description: A reference to the shipping method.

delivery_category.name: delivery_category
delivery_category.description: The general classification of the delivery method.

discounted_price.name: discounted_price
discounted_price.description: The pre-tax shipping price with discounts applied in shop currency.

discounted_price_set.name: discounted_price_set
discounted_price_set.description: The pre-tax shipping price with discounts applied (JSON) in presentment and shop currencies.

order_id.name: order_id
order_id.description: ID of the associated order.

phone.name: phone
phone.description: The phone number at the shipping address.

price.name: price
price.description: Returns the price of the shipping line in shop currency.

price_set.name: price_set
price_set.description: Returns the price of the shipping line (JSON) in shop and presentment currencies.

is_third_party_required.name: is_third_party_required
is_third_party_required.description: The fulfillment service requested for the shipping method. Present if the shipping method requires processing by a third party fulfillment service.

source.name: source
source.description: Returns the rate source for the shipping line.

title.name: title
title.description: Returns the title of the shipping line.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

billing_address_province.name: billing_address_province
billing_address_province.description: The name of the region (province, state, prefecture, …) of the billing address.

billing_address_province_code.name: billing_address_province_code
billing_address_province_code.description: The two-letter abbreviation of the region of the billing address.

billing_address_zip.name: billing_address_zip
billing_address_zip.description: The postal code (zip, postcode, Eircode, …) of the billing address.

browser_ip.name: browser_ip
browser_ip.description: The IP address of the browser used by the customer when they placed the order.

has_buyer_accepted_marketing.name: has_buyer_accepted_marketing
has_buyer_accepted_marketing.description: Whether the customer consented to receive email updates from the shop.

cancel_reason.name: cancel_reason
cancel_reason.description: The reason why the order was canceled.

cancelled_timestamp.name: cancelled_timestamp
cancelled_timestamp.description: The date and time when the order was canceled.

cart_token.name: cart_token
cart_token.description: The ID of the cart that's associated with the order.

closed_timestamp.name: closed_timestamp
closed_timestamp.description: The date and time when the order was closed (archived).

created_timestamp.name: created_timestamp
created_timestamp.description: The autogenerated date and time when the order was created in Shopify.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: The three-letter code for the shop currency.

customer_id.name: customer_id
customer_id.description: The ID of the order's customer.

financial_status.name: financial_status
financial_status.description: The status of payments associated with the order. Can only be set when the order is created

fulfillment_status.name: fulfillment_status
fulfillment_status.description: The order's status in terms of fulfilled line items.

order_id.name: order_id
order_id.description: The ID of the order, used for API purposes. This is different from the order_number property, which is the ID used by the shop owner and customer.

landing_site_base_url.name: landing_site_base_url
landing_site_base_url.description: The URL for the page where the buyer landed when they entered the shop.

location_id.name: location_id
location_id.description: The ID of the physical location where the order was processed.

name.name: name
name.description: The order name, generated by combining the order_number property with the order prefix and suffix that are set in the merchant's general settings.

note.name: note
note.description: An optional note that a shop owner can attach to the order.

number.name: number
number.description: The order's position in the shop's count of orders. Numbers are sequential and start at 1.

order_number.name: order_number
order_number.description: The order 's position in the shop's count of orders starting at 1001. Order numbers are sequential and start at 1001.

processed_timestamp.name: processed_timestamp
processed_timestamp.description: The date and time when an order was processed. This value is the date that appears on your orders and that's used in the analytic reports.

referring_site.name: referring_site
referring_site.description: The website where the customer clicked a link to the shop.

shipping_address_address_1.name: shipping_address_address_1
shipping_address_address_1.description: The street address of the shipping address.

shipping_address_address_2.name: shipping_address_address_2
shipping_address_address_2.description: An optional additional field for the street address of the shipping address.

shipping_address_city.name: shipping_address_city
shipping_address_city.description: The city, town, or village of the shipping address.

shipping_address_company.name: shipping_address_company
shipping_address_company.description: The company of the person associated with the shipping address.

shipping_address_country.name: shipping_address_country
shipping_address_country.description: The name of the country of the shipping address.

shipping_address_country_code.name: shipping_address_country_code
shipping_address_country_code.description: The two-letter code (ISO 3166-1 format) for the country of the shipping address.

shipping_address_first_name.name: shipping_address_first_name
shipping_address_first_name.description: The first name of the person associated with the shipping address.

shipping_address_last_name.name: shipping_address_last_name
shipping_address_last_name.description: The last name of the person associated with the shipping address.

shipping_address_latitude.name: shipping_address_latitude
shipping_address_latitude.description: The latitude of the shipping address.

shipping_address_longitude.name: shipping_address_longitude
shipping_address_longitude.description: The longitude of the shipping address.

shipping_address_name.name: shipping_address_name
shipping_address_name.description: The full name of the person associated with the payment method.

shipping_address_phone.name: shipping_address_phone
shipping_address_phone.description: The phone number at the shipping address.

shipping_address_province.name: shipping_address_province
shipping_address_province.description: The name of the region (province, state, prefecture, …) of the shipping address.

shipping_address_province_code.name: shipping_address_province_code
shipping_address_province_code.description: The two-letter abbreviation of the region of the shipping address.

shipping_address_zip.name: shipping_address_zip
shipping_address_zip.description: The postal code (zip, postcode, Eircode, …) of the shipping address.

source_name.name: source_name
source_name.description: Where the order originated. Can be set only during order creation, and is not writeable afterwards.

subtotal_price.name: subtotal_price
subtotal_price.description: The price of the order in the shop currency after discounts but before shipping, taxes, and tips.

has_taxes_included.name: has_taxes_included
has_taxes_included.description: Whether taxes are included in the order subtotal.

is_test_order.name: is_test_order
is_test_order.description: Whether this is a test order.

token.name: token
token.description: A unique token for the order.

total_discounts.name: total_discounts
total_discounts.description: The total discounts applied to the price of the order in the shop currency.

total_line_items_price.name: total_line_items_price
total_line_items_price.description: The sum of all line item prices in the shop currency.

total_price.name: total_price
total_price.description: The sum of all line item prices, discounts, shipping, taxes, and tips in the shop currency. Must be positive.

total_tax.name: total_tax
total_tax.description: The sum of all the taxes applied to the order in th shop currency. Must be positive).

total_weight.name: total_weight
total_weight.description: The sum of all line item weights in grams.

updated_timestamp.name: updated_timestamp
updated_timestamp.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the order was last modified.

user_id.name: user_id
user_id.description: The ID of the user logged into Shopify POS who processed the order, if applicable.

total_shipping_price_set.name: total_shipping_price_set
total_shipping_price_set.description: The total shipping price of the order, excluding discounts and returns, in shop and presentment currencies. If taxes_included is set to true, then total_shipping_price_set includes taxes.

checkout_token.name: checkout_token
checkout_token.description: A unique value when referencing the checkout that's associated with the order.

customer_locale.name: customer_locale
customer_locale.description: A two-letter or three-letter language code, optionally followed by a region modifier.

is_deleted.name: is_deleted
is_deleted.description: Boolean representing whether the record was soft-deleted in Shopify.

total_tip_received.name: total_tip_received
total_tip_received.description: The sum of all the tips in the order in the shop currency.

client_details_user_agent.name: client_details_user_agent
client_details_user_agent.description: Details of the browsing client, including software and operating versions.

total_tax_set.name: total_tax_set
total_tax_set.description: The total tax applied to the order in shop and presentment currencies.

total_discounts_set.name: total_discounts_set
total_discounts_set.description: The total discounts applied to the price of the order in shop and presentment currencies.

presentment_currency.name: presentment_currency
presentment_currency.description: The presentment currency that was used to display prices to the customer.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The ID of the order placed on the originating platform. This value doesn't correspond to the Shopify ID that's generated from a completed draft.

total_line_items_price_set.name: total_line_items_price_set
total_line_items_price_set.description: The total of all line item prices in shop and presentment currencies.

total_price_set.name: total_price_set
total_price_set.description: The total price of the order in shop and presentment currencies.

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__order.raw_code:
{{ config(enabled=var('shopify_api', 'rest') == 'rest') }}

{% set source_columns_in_relation = adapter.get_columns_in_relation(ref('stg_shopify__order_tmp')) %}

with base as (

    select * 
    from {{ ref('stg_shopify__order_tmp') }}

),

fields as (

    select
    
        {{
            fivetran_utils.fill_staging_columns(
                source_columns=source_columns_in_relation,
                staging_columns=get_order_columns()
            )
        }}

        {{ fivetran_utils.source_relation(
            union_schema_variable='shopify_union_schemas', 
            union_database_variable='shopify_union_databases') 
        }}

    from base

),

final as (

    select 
        id as order_id,
        user_id,
        total_discounts,
        {{ shopify_source.json_to_string("total_discounts_set", source_columns_in_relation) }} as total_discounts_set,
        total_line_items_price,
        {{ shopify_source.json_to_string("total_line_items_price_set", source_columns_in_relation) }} as total_line_items_price_set,
        total_price,
        {{ shopify_source.json_to_string("total_price_set", source_columns_in_relation) }} as total_price_set,
        {{ shopify_source.json_to_string("total_tax_set", source_columns_in_relation) }} as total_tax_set,
        total_tax,
        source_name,
        subtotal_price,
        taxes_included as has_taxes_included,
        total_weight,
        total_tip_received,
        landing_site_base_url,
        location_id,
        name,
        note,
        number,
        order_number,
        cancel_reason,
        cart_token,
        checkout_token,
        {{ shopify_source.fivetran_convert_timezone(column='cast(created_at as ' ~ dbt.type_timestamp() ~ ')', target_tz=var('shopify_timezone', "UTC"), source_tz="UTC") }} as created_timestamp,
        {{ shopify_source.fivetran_convert_timezone(column='cast(cancelled_at as ' ~ dbt.type_timestamp() ~ ')', target_tz=var('shopify_timezone', "UTC"), source_tz="UTC") }} as cancelled_timestamp,
        {{ shopify_source.fivetran_convert_timezone(column='cast(closed_at as ' ~ dbt.type_timestamp() ~ ')', target_tz=var('shopify_timezone', "UTC"), source_tz="UTC") }} as closed_timestamp,
        {{ shopify_source.fivetran_convert_timezone(column='cast(processed_at as ' ~ dbt.type_timestamp() ~ ')', target_tz=var('shopify_timezone', "UTC"), source_tz="UTC") }} as processed_timestamp,
        {{ shopify_source.fivetran_convert_timezone(column='cast(updated_at as ' ~ dbt.type_timestamp() ~ ')', target_tz=var('shopify_timezone', "UTC"), source_tz="UTC") }} as updated_timestamp,
        currency,
        customer_id,
        lower(email) as email,
        financial_status,
        fulfillment_status,
        referring_site,
        billing_address_address_1,
        billing_address_address_2,
        billing_address_city,
        billing_address_company,
        billing_address_country,
        billing_address_country_code,
        billing_address_first_name,
        billing_address_last_name,
        billing_address_latitude,
        billing_address_longitude,
        billing_address_name,
        billing_address_phone,
        billing_address_province,
        billing_address_province_code,
        billing_address_zip,
        browser_ip,
        {{ shopify_source.json_to_string("total_shipping_price_set", source_columns_in_relation) }} as total_shipping_price_set,
        shipping_address_address_1,
        shipping_address_address_2,
        shipping_address_city,
        shipping_address_company,
        shipping_address_country,
        shipping_address_country_code,
        shipping_address_first_name,
        shipping_address_last_name,
        shipping_address_latitude,
        shipping_address_longitude,
        shipping_address_name,
        shipping_address_phone,
        shipping_address_province,
        shipping_address_province_code,
        shipping_address_zip,
        token,
        app_id,
        checkout_id,
        client_details_user_agent,
        customer_locale,
        order_status_url,
        presentment_currency,
        test as is_test_order,
        _fivetran_deleted as is_deleted,
        buyer_accepts_marketing as has_buyer_accepted_marketing,
        confirmed as is_confirmed,
        {{ shopify_source.fivetran_convert_timezone(column='cast(_fivetran_synced as ' ~ dbt.type_timestamp() ~ ')', target_tz=var('shopify_timezone', "UTC"), source_tz="UTC") }} as _fivetran_synced,
        source_relation

        {{ fivetran_utils.fill_pass_through_columns('order_pass_through_columns') }}

    from fields
)

select * 
from final
where not coalesce(is_test_order, false)
and not coalesce(is_deleted, false)

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__transa.name: stg_shopify__transaction
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__transa.description: Each record represents a transaction in Shopify.

order_id.name: order_id
order_id.description: The ID for the order that the transaction is associated with.

refund_id.name: refund_id
refund_id.description: The ID associated with a refund in the refund table.

amount.name: amount
amount.description: The amount of money included in the transaction.

authorization_code.name: authorization_code
authorization_code.description: The authorization code associated with the transaction.

created_timestamp.name: created_timestamp
created_timestamp.description: The date and time when the transaction was created.

processed_timestamp.name: processed_timestamp
processed_timestamp.description: The date and time when a transaction was processed.

gateway.name: gateway
gateway.description: The name of the gateway the transaction was issued through.

message.name: message
message.description: A string generated by the payment provider with additional information about why the transaction succeeded or failed.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: The three-letter code (ISO 4217 format) for the currency used for the payment.

location_id.name: location_id
location_id.description: The ID of the physical location where the transaction was processed.

parent_id.name: parent_id
parent_id.description: The ID of an associated transaction.

payment_avs_result_code.name: payment_avs_result_code
payment_avs_result_code.description: The response code from the address verification system.

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__discou.name: stg_shopify__discount_code_basic
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__discou.description: Table storing metadata about basic discount codes created by merchants.

discount_code_id.name: discount_code_id
discount_code_id.description: The unique ID for the discount code.

title.name: title
title.description: The display name for the discount code.

status.name: status
status.description: The status of the discount code (e.g., `enabled`, `disabled`, `expired`).

applies_once_per_customer.name: applies_once_per_customer
applies_once_per_customer.description: Boolean representing whether the discount code is limited to one use per customer.

usage_limit.name: usage_limit
usage_limit.description: The total number of times the discount code can be used.

usage_count.name: usage_count
usage_count.description: The number of times the discount code has been used.

codes_count.name: codes_count
codes_count.description: The total number of redeemable codes generated for this discount.

codes_precision.name: codes_precision
codes_precision.description: Indicates the precision or type of generated codes (e.g., exact vs. bulk).

combines_with_order_discounts.name: combines_with_order_discounts
combines_with_order_discounts.description: Whether this discount can be combined with other order-level discounts.

combines_with_product_discounts.name: combines_with_product_discounts
combines_with_product_discounts.description: Whether this discount can be combined with product-level discounts.

combines_with_shipping_discounts.name: combines_with_shipping_discounts
combines_with_shipping_discounts.description: Whether this discount can be combined with shipping discounts.

customer_selection_all_customers.name: customer_selection_all_customers
customer_selection_all_customers.description: Boolean indicating whether the discount is available to all customers.

recurring_cycle_limit.name: recurring_cycle_limit
recurring_cycle_limit.description: The number of billing cycles this discount applies to (for subscription products).

total_sales_amount.name: total_sales_amount
total_sales_amount.description: The total sales amount that resulted from the usage of this discount.

created_at.name: created_at
created_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the discount code was created.

updated_at.name: updated_at
updated_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the discount code was last updated.

starts_at.name: starts_at
starts_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the discount code becomes active.

ends_at.name: ends_at
ends_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the discount code expires.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__fulfil.name: stg_shopify__fulfillment
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__fulfil.description: A fulfillment order represents a group of one or more items in an order that will be fulfilled from the same location.  A fulfillment represents work that is completed as part of a fulfillment order and can include one or more items.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

created_at.name: created_at
created_at.description: The date and time when the fulfillment was created. The API returns this value in ISO 8601 format.

location_id.name: location_id
location_id.description: The unique identifier of the location that the fulfillment was processed at.

name.name: name
name.description: The uniquely identifying fulfillment name, consisting of two parts separated by a .. The first part represents the order name and the second part represents the fulfillment number.  The fulfillment number automatically increments depending on how many fulfillments are in an order (e.g. #1001.1, #1001.2).

order_id.name: order_id
order_id.description: The unique numeric identifier for the order.

service.name: service
service.description: The fulfillment service associated with the fulfillment.

shipment_status.name: shipment_status
shipment_status.description: The current shipment status of the fulfillment. Valid values include: - label_printed: A label for the shipment was purchased and printed. - label_purchased: A label for the shipment was purchased, but not printed. - attempted_delivery: Delivery of the shipment was attempted, but unable to be completed. - ready_for_pickup: The shipment is ready for pickup at a shipping depot. - confirmed: The carrier is aware of the shipment, but hasn't received it yet. - in_transit: The shipment is being transported between shipping facilities on the way to its destination. - out_for_delivery: The shipment is being delivered to its final destination. - delivered: The shipment was successfully delivered. - failure: Something went wrong when pulling tracking information for the shipment, such as the tracking number was invalid or the shipment was canceled.

status.name: status
status.description: The status of the fulfillment. Valid values include: - pending: Shopify has created the fulfillment and is waiting for the third-party fulfillment service to transition it to 'open' or 'success'. - open: The fulfillment has been acknowledged by the service and is in processing. - success: The fulfillment was successful. - cancelled: The fulfillment was cancelled. - error: There was an error with the fulfillment request. - failure: The fulfillment request failed.

tracking_company.name: tracking_company
tracking_company.description: The name of the tracking company.

tracking_number.name: tracking_number
tracking_number.description: Primary tracking number for the order.

tracking_numbers.name: tracking_numbers
tracking_numbers.description: A list of tracking numbers, provided by the shipping company.

tracking_urls.name: tracking_urls
tracking_urls.description: The URLs of tracking pages for the fulfillment.

updated_at.name: updated_at
updated_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the fulfillment was last modified.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__metafi.name: stg_shopify__metafield
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__metafi.description: Metafields are a flexible way to attach additional information to a Shopify resource (e.g. Product, Collection, etc.). Some examples of data stored using metafields include specifications, size charts,  downloadable documents, release dates, images, or part numbers. Metafields are identified by an owner resource, a namespace, and a key and they store a value along with type information for that context.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

created_at.name: created_at
created_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the metafield was created.

description.name: description
description.description: A description of the information that the metafield contains.

metafield_id.name: metafield_id
metafield_id.description: The unique ID of the metafield.

key.name: key

discount_code_id.name: discount_code_id

status.name: status

applies_once_per_customer.description: Boolean representing whether the discount code is limited to one use per customer.

usage_limit.name: usage_limit

usage_count.name: usage_count

combines_with_product_discounts.name: combines_with_product_discounts

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__tender.description: Each tender transaction represents money passing between the merchant and a customer. A tender transaction with a positive amount  represents a transaction where the customer paid money to the merchant. A negative amount represents a transaction where the  merchant refunded money back to the customer. Tender transactions represent transactions that modify the shop's balance.

_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

amount.name: amount
amount.description: The amount of the tender transaction in the shop's currency.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: The three-letter code (ISO 4217 format) for the currency used for the tender transaction.

order_id.name: order_id
order_id.description: The ID of the order that the tender transaction belongs to.

payment_method.name: payment_method
payment_method.description: Information about the payment method used for this transaction. Valid values include: - credit_card - cash - android_pay - apple_pay - google_pay - samsung_pay - shopify_pay - amazon - klarna - paypal - unknown - other

processed_at.name: processed_at
processed_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the tender transaction was processed.

remote_reference.name: remote_reference
remote_reference.description: The remote (gateway) reference associated with the tender.

user_id.name: user_id
user_id.description: The ID of the user logged into the Shopify POS device that processed the tender transaction, if applicable.

source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__shop.name: stg_shopify__shop
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__shop.description: The Shop resource is a collection of general business and store management settings and information about the store.

is_deleted.name: is_deleted
is_deleted.description: Boolean representing whether the record was soft-deleted in Shopify.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

address_2.name: address_2
address_2.description: The optional second line of the shop's street address.

has_checkout_api_supported.name: has_checkout_api_supported
has_checkout_api_supported.description: Boolean representing whether the shop is capable of accepting payments directly through the Checkout API.

cookie_consent_level.name: cookie_consent_level
cookie_consent_level.description: The cookie consent level defined on the shop's online store.

country.name: country
country.description: The shop's country. In most cases, this value matches the country_code.

country_code.name: country_code
country_code.description: The two-letter country code corresponding to the shop's country.

has_county_taxes.name: has_county_taxes
has_county_taxes.description: Boolean representing whether the shop is applying taxes on a per-county basis. Only applicable to shops based in the US. Either `true` or `null` (not false, according to Shopify API docs).

created_at.name: created_at
created_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601) when the shop was created.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: The three-letter code (ISO 4217 format) for the shop's default currency.

customer_email.name: customer_email
customer_email.description: The contact email used for communication between the shop owner and the customer.

is_eligible_for_card_reader_giveaway.name: is_eligible_for_card_reader_giveaway
is_eligible_for_card_reader_giveaway.description: Boolean representing whether the shop is eligible to receive a free credit card reader from Shopify.

is_eligible_for_payments.name: is_eligible_for_payments
is_eligible_for_payments.description: Boolean representing whether the shop is eligible to use Shopify Payments.

email.name: email
email.description: The contact email used for communication between Shopify and the shop owner.

enabled_presentment_currencies.name: enabled_presentment_currencies
enabled_presentment_currencies.description: An array of of enabled currencies (ISO 4217 format) that the shop accepts. Merchants can enable currencies from their Shopify Payments settings in the Shopify Admin.

google_apps_domain.name: google_apps_domain
google_apps_domain.description: The GSuite URL for the store, if applicable.

is_google_apps_login_enabled.name: is_google_apps_login_enabled
is_google_apps_login_enabled.description: Boolean representing whether the GSuite login is enabled. Shops with this feature will be able to log in through the GSuite login page. Valid values are `true` and `null`.

has_discounts.name: has_discounts
has_discounts.description: Boolean representing whether any active discounts exist for the shop.

has_gift_cards.name: has_gift_cards
has_gift_cards.description: Boolean representing whether any active gift cards exist for the shop.

has_storefront.name: has_storefront
has_storefront.description: Boolean representing whether this shop has an online store.

iana_timezone.name: iana_timezone
iana_timezone.description: The name of the timezone assigned by the [IANA](https://www.iana.org/time-zones).

shop_id.name: shop_id
shop_id.description: The ID for the shop. A 64-bit unsigned integer.

latitude.name: latitude
latitude.description: The latitude of the shop's location.

longitude.name: longitude
longitude.description: The longitude of the shop's location.

money_format.name: money_format
money_format.description: A string representing the way currency is formatted when the currency isn't specified.

money_in_emails_format.name: money_in_emails_format
money_in_emails_format.description: A string representing the way currency is formatted in email notifications when the currency isn't specified.

money_with_currency_format.name: money_with_currency_format
money_with_currency_format.description: A string representing the way currency is formatted when the currency is specified.

money_with_currency_in_emails_format.name: money_with_currency_in_emails_format
money_with_currency_in_emails_format.description: A string representing the way currency is formatted in email notifications when the currency is specified.

name.name: name
name.description: The name of the shop.

is_password_enabled.name: is_password_enabled
is_password_enabled.description: Boolean representing whether the password protection page is enabled on the shop's online store.

phone.name: phone
phone.description: The contact phone number for the shop.

plan_display_name.name: plan_display_name
plan_display_name.description: The display name of the Shopify plan the shop is on.

plan_name.name: plan_name
plan_name.description: The name of the Shopify plan the shop is on.

is_pre_launch_enabled.name: is_pre_launch_enabled
is_pre_launch_enabled.description: Boolean representing whether the pre-launch page is enabled on the shop's online store.

primary_locale.name: primary_locale
primary_locale.description: The shop's primary locale, as configured in the language settings of the shop's theme.

province.name: province
province.description: The shop's normalized province or state name.

province_code.name: province_code
province_code.description: The two- or three-letter code for the shop's province or state.

is_extra_payments_agreement_required.name: is_extra_payments_agreement_required
is_extra_payments_agreement_required.description: Boolean representing whether the shop requires an extra Shopify Payments agreement.

is_setup_required.name: is_setup_required
is_setup_required.description: Boolean representing whether the shop has any outstanding setup steps.

shop_owner.name: shop_owner
shop_owner.description: The username of the shop owner.

source.name: source
source.description: The handle of the partner account that referred the merchant to Shopify, if applicable.

has_shipping_taxes.name: has_shipping_taxes
has_shipping_taxes.description: Boolean representing whether taxes are charged for shipping. Valid values are true or false.

has_taxes_included_in_price.name: has_taxes_included_in_price
has_taxes_included_in_price.description: Boolean representing whether applicable taxes are included in product prices. Valid values are true or null.

timezone.name: timezone
timezone.description: The name of the timezone the shop is in.

updated_at.name: updated_at
updated_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601) when the shop was last updated.

weight_unit.name: weight_unit
weight_unit.description: The default unit of weight measurement for the shop.

zip.name: zip
zip.description: The shop's zip or postal code.

source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

{{ config(enabled=var('shopify_api', 'rest') == 'rest') }}

{% set source_columns_in_relation = adapter.get_columns_in_relation(ref('stg_shopify__shop_tmp')) %}

with base as (

    select * 
    from {{ ref('stg_shopify__shop_tmp') }}
),

fields as (

    select
        {{
            fivetran_utils.fill_staging_columns(
                source_columns=source_columns_in_relation,
                staging_columns=get_shop_columns()
            )
        }}

        {{ fivetran_utils.source_relation(
            union_schema_variable='shopify_union_schemas', 
            union_database_variable='shopify_union_databases') 
        }}

    from base
),

final as (
    
    select 
        id as shop_id,
        name,
        _fivetran_deleted as is_deleted,
        address_1,
        address_2,
        city,
        province,
        province_code,
        country,
        country_code,
        country_name,
        zip,
        latitude,
        longitude,
        case when county_taxes is null then false else county_taxes end as has_county_taxes,
        currency,
        {{ shopify_source.json_to_string("enabled_presentment_currencies", source_columns_in_relation) }} as enabled_presentment_currencies,
        customer_email,
        email,
        domain,
        phone,
        timezone,
        iana_timezone,

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__invent.name: stg_shopify__inventory_level
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__invent.description:
An inventory level represents the quantities of an inventory item for a location.
Each inventory level belongs to one inventory item and has one location. For every location where an inventory item can be stocked, there's an inventory level that represents  the inventory item's quantities relating to that location.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

available_quantity.name: available_quantity
available_quantity.description: (DEPRECATED 2025-01-06) The available quantity of an inventory item at the inventory level's associated location. Returns null if the inventory item is not tracked.

inventory_item_id.name: inventory_item_id
inventory_item_id.description: The ID of the inventory item associated with the inventory level.

inventory_level_id.name: inventory_level_id
inventory_level_id.description: The ID of the inventory level record.

location_id.name: location_id
location_id.description: The ID of the location that the inventory level belongs to.

updated_at.name: updated_at
updated_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the inventory level was last modified.

can_deactivate.name: can_deactivate
can_deactivate.description: Indicates whether the inventory item can be deactivated at the location.

created_at.name: created_at
created_at.description: The date and time when the inventory level was created.

deactivation_alert.name: deactivation_alert
deactivation_alert.description: Provides an alert message when the inventory item is deactivated at the location.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

created_by_id.name: created_by_id
created_by_id.description: The internal ID of the app or user that created the redeem code.

created_by_title.name: created_by_title
created_by_title.description: The name or title of the creator of the redeem code (typically an app name).

discount_id.name: discount_id
discount_id.description: The unique ID of the parent discount associated with this redeem code.

discount_type.name: discount_type
discount_type.description: The type of discount the redeem code is associated with (e.g., `discount_code_basic`, `discount_code_app`).

source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__custom.name: stg_shopify__customer
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__custom.description: Each record represents a customer in Shopify.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

marketing_consent_state.name: marketing_consent_state
marketing_consent_state.description: Field indicating if the customer has consented to receive marketing material via email. Coalescing of the new `email_marketing_consent_state` field and the deprecated `accepts_marketing` field. Records with the old field will be marked with '(legacy)'.

marketing_opt_in_level.name: marketing_opt_in_level
marketing_opt_in_level.description: The marketing subscription opt-in level, as described in the M3AAWG Sender Best Common Practices, that the customer gave when they consented to receive marketing material by email.

marketing_consent_updated_at.name: marketing_consent_updated_at
marketing_consent_updated_at.description: The date and time when the customer consented to receive marketing material by email. If no date is provided, then the date and time when the consent information was sent is used.

created_timestamp.name: created_timestamp
created_timestamp.description: The date and time when the customer was created.

default_address_id.name: default_address_id
default_address_id.description: The default address for the customer.

email.name: email
email.description: The unique email address of the customer. Attempting to assign the same email address to multiple customers returns an error.

customer_id.name: customer_id
customer_id.description: A unique identifier for the customer.

orders_count.name: orders_count
orders_count.description: The number of orders associated with this customer.

phone.name: phone
phone.description: The unique phone number (E.164 format) for this customer. Attempting to assign the same phone number to multiple customers returns an error.

account_state.name: account_state
account_state.description: The state of the customer's account with a shop.

is_tax_exempt.name: is_tax_exempt
is_tax_exempt.description: Whether the customer is exempt from paying taxes on their order. If true, then taxes won't be applied to an order at checkout. If false, then taxes will be applied at checkout.

total_spent.name: total_spent
total_spent.description: The total amount of money that the customer has spent across their order history.

updated_timestamp.name: updated_timestamp
updated_timestamp.description: The date and time when the customer information was last updated.

is_verified_email.name: is_verified_email
is_verified_email.description: Whether the customer has verified their email address.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: The three-letter code (ISO 4217 format) for the currency that the customer used when they paid for their last order. Defaults to the shop currency. Returns the shop currency for test orders.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__custom.raw_code:
{{ config(enabled=var('shopify_api', 'rest') == 'rest') }}

with base as (

    select * 
    from {{ ref('stg_shopify__customer_tmp') }}

),

fields as (

    select
    
        {{
            fivetran_utils.fill_staging_columns(
                source_columns=adapter.get_columns_in_relation(ref('stg_shopify__customer_tmp')),
                staging_columns=get_customer_columns()
            )
        }}

        {{ fivetran_utils.source_relation(
            union_schema_variable='shopify_union_schemas', 
            union_database_variable='shopify_union_databases') 
        }}

    from base

),

final as (

    select 
        id as customer_id,
        lower(email) as email,
        first_name,
        last_name,
        orders_count,
        default_address_id,
        phone,
        lower(state) as account_state,
        tax_exempt as is_tax_exempt,
        total_spent,
        verified_email as is_verified_email,
        note,
        currency,
        case 
            when email_marketing_consent_state is null then
                case 
                    when accepts_marketing is null then null
                    when accepts_marketing then 'subscribed (legacy)' 
                    else 'not_subscribed (legacy)' end
            else lower(email_marketing_consent_state) end as marketing_consent_state,
        lower(coalesce(email_marketing_consent_opt_in_level, marketing_opt_in_level)) as marketing_opt_in_level,

        {{ shopify_source.fivetran_convert_timezone(column='cast(coalesce(accepts_marketing_updated_at, email_marketing_consent_consent_updated_at) as ' ~ dbt.type_timestamp() ~ ')', target_tz=var('shopify_timezone', "UTC"), source_tz="UTC") }} as marketing_consent_updated_at,
        {{ shopify_source.fivetran_convert_timezone(column='cast(created_at as ' ~ dbt.type_timestamp() ~ ')', target_tz=var('shopify_timezone', "UTC"), source_tz="UTC") }} as created_timestamp,
        {{ shopify_source.fivetran_convert_timezone(column='cast(updated_at as ' ~ dbt.type_timestamp() ~ ')', target_tz=var('shopify_timezone', "UTC"), source_tz="UTC") }} as updated_timestamp,
        {{ shopify_source.fivetran_convert_timezone(column='cast(_fivetran_synced as ' ~ dbt.type_timestamp() ~ ')', target_tz=var('shopify_timezone', "UTC"), source_tz="UTC") }} as _fivetran_synced,
        source_relation
        
        {{ fivetran_utils.fill_pass_through_columns('customer_pass_through_columns') }}

    from fields
    
)

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__collec.name: stg_shopify__collection
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__collec.description: A collection is a grouping of products that merchants can create to make their stores easier to browse. Merchants can create collections by selecting products individually or by defining rules that automatically determine whether products are included (aka a "smart collection").

is_deleted.name: is_deleted
is_deleted.description: Boolean representing whether the record was soft-deleted in Shopify.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

rule_logic.name: rule_logic
rule_logic.description: Whether the `rules` are disjunctive (logical `OR`) or conjunctive (logical `AND`)

handle.name: handle
handle.description: A unique, human-readable string for the collection automatically generated from its title. This is used in themes by the Liquid templating language to refer to the collection.

published_at.name: published_at
published_at.description: The time and date (ISO 8601 format) when the collection was made visible. Returns null for a hidden collection.

published_scope.name: published_scope
published_scope.description: Whether the collection is published to the Point of Sale channel. Valid values `web` (the collection is published to the Online Store channel but not published to the Point of Sale channel) and `global` (the collection is published to both the Online Store channel and the Point of Sale channel).

rules.name: rules
rules.description: An array of rules that define what products go into the smart collection. Each rule (`column` -- `relation` --> `condition`) has these properties: - `column`: the property of a product being used to populate the smart collection. Ex: 'tag', 'type', 'vendor', 'variant_price', etc. - `relation`: The comparative relationship between the column choice, and the condition ('equals', 'contains', 'greater_than', etc.) - condition: Select products for a smart collection using a condition. Values are either strings or numbers, depending on the relation value. See the [Shopify docs](https://shopify.dev/api/admin-rest/2022-10/resources/smartcollection#resource-object) for more.

sort_order.name: sort_order
sort_order.description: The order of the products in the collection. Valid values incline - `alpha-asc`: The products are sorted alphabetically from A to Z. - `alpha-des`: The products are sorted alphabetically from Z to A. - `best-selling`: The products are sorted by number of sales. - `created`: The products are sorted by the date they were created, from oldest to newest. - `created-desc`: The products are sorted by the date they were created, from newest to oldest. - `manual`: The products are manually sorted by the shop owner. - `price-asc`: The products are sorted by price from lowest to highest. - `price-desc`: The products are sorted by price from highest to lowest.

title.name: title
title.description: The name of the collection

updated_at.name: updated_at
updated_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the collection was last modified.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

allocation_method.description: The method by which the discount is allocated. Valid values include `each` (applies the discount to each eligible item) and `across` (spreads the discount value across eligible items).

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__produc.name: stg_shopify__product_variant
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__produc.description: Each record represents a product variant in Shopify

barcode.name: barcode
barcode.description: The barcode, UPC, or ISBN number for the product.

compare_at_price.name: compare_at_price
compare_at_price.description: The original price of the item before an adjustment or a sale in shop currency

created_timestamp.name: created_timestamp
created_timestamp.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the product variant was created.

fulfillment_service.name: fulfillment_service
fulfillment_service.description: (DEPRECATED 2025-01-06) The fulfillment service associated with the product variant.

grams.name: grams
grams.description: (DEPRECATED 2025-01-06) The weight of the product variant in grams.

variant_id.name: variant_id
variant_id.description: The unique numeric identifier for the product variant.

inventory_item_id.name: inventory_item_id
inventory_item_id.description: The unique identifier for the inventory item, which is used in the Inventory API to query for inventory information.

inventory_management.name: inventory_management
inventory_management.description: (DEPRECATED 2025-01-06) The fulfillment service that tracks the number of items in stock for the product variant.

inventory_policy.name: inventory_policy
inventory_policy.description: Whether customers are allowed to place an order for the product variant when it's out of stock.

inventory_quantity.name: inventory_quantity
inventory_quantity.description: An aggregate of inventory across all locations. To adjust inventory at a specific location, use the InventoryLevel resource.

option_1.name: option_1
option_1.description: (DEPRECATED 2025-01-06) The custom properties that a shop owner uses to define product variants. You can define three options for a product variant: option1, option2, option3.

option_2.name: option_2
option_2.description: (DEPRECATED 2025-01-06) The custom properties that a shop owner uses to define product variants. You can define three options for a product variant: option1, option2, option3.

option_3.name: option_3
option_3.description: (DEPRECATED 2025-01-06) The custom properties that a shop owner uses to define product variants. You can define three options for a product variant: option1, option2, option3.

position.name: position
position.description: The order of the product variant in the list of product variants. The first position in the list is 1. The position of variants is indicated by the order in which they are listed.

price.name: price
price.description: The price of the product variant.

product_id.name: product_id
product_id.description: The unique numeric identifier for the product.

sku.name: sku
sku.description: A unique identifier for the product variant in the shop. Required in order to connect to a FulfillmentService.

is_taxable.name: is_taxable
is_taxable.description: Whether a tax is charged when the product variant is sold.

tax_code.name: tax_code
tax_code.description: This parameter applies only to the stores that have the Avalara AvaTax app installed. Specifies the Avalara tax code for the product variant.

title.name: title
title.description: The title of the product variant. The title field is a concatenation of the option1, option2, and option3 fields. You can only update title indirectly using the option fields.

updated_timestamp.name: updated_timestamp
updated_timestamp.description: The date and time when the product variant was last modified. Gets returned in ISO 8601 format.

weight.name: weight
weight.description: (DEPRECATED 2025-01-06) The weight of the product variant in the unit system specified with weight_unit.

weight_unit.name: weight_unit
weight_unit.description: (DEPRECATED 2025-01-06) The unit of measurement that applies to the product variant's weight. If you don't specify a value for weight_unit, then the shop's default unit of measurement is applied. Valid values: g, kg, oz, and lb.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

is_available_for_sale.name: is_available_for_sale
is_available_for_sale.description: Indicates whether the product variant is available for sale.

display_name.name: display_name
display_name.description: The display name of the variant, based on the product's title and variant's title.

legacy_resource_id.name: legacy_resource_id
legacy_resource_id.description: The ID of the corresponding resource in the REST Admin API.

has_components_required.name: has_components_required
has_components_required.description: Indicates whether a product variant requires components.

sellable_online_quantity.name: sellable_online_quantity
sellable_online_quantity.description: The total sellable quantity of the variant for online channels.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__produc.raw_code:
{{ config(enabled=var('shopify_api', 'rest') == 'rest') }}

with base as (

    select * 
    from {{ ref('stg_shopify__product_variant_tmp') }}

),

fields as (

    select
    
        {{
            fivetran_utils.fill_staging_columns(
                source_columns=adapter.get_columns_in_relation(ref('stg_shopify__product_variant_tmp')),
                staging_columns=get_product_variant_columns()
            )
        }}

        {{ fivetran_utils.source_relation(
            union_schema_variable='shopify_union_schemas', 
            union_database_variable='shopify_union_databases') 
        }}

    from base

),

final as (

    select
        id as variant_id,
        product_id,
        inventory_item_id,
        title,
        price,
        sku,
        position,
        inventory_policy,
        compare_at_price,
        fulfillment_service,
        inventory_management,
        taxable as is_taxable,
        barcode,
        grams,
        coalesce(inventory_quantity, old_inventory_quantity) as inventory_quantity,
        available_for_sale as is_available_for_sale,
        display_name,
        legacy_resource_id,
        requires_components as has_components_required,
        sellable_online_quantity,
        weight,
        weight_unit,
        option_1,
        option_2,
        option_3,
        tax_code,
        {{ shopify_source.fivetran_convert_timezone(column='cast(created_at as ' ~ dbt.type_timestamp() ~ ')', target_tz=var('shopify_timezone', "UTC"), source_tz="UTC") }} as created_timestamp,
        {{ shopify_source.fivetran_convert_timezone(column='cast(updated_at as ' ~ dbt.type_timestamp() ~ ')', target_tz=var('shopify_timezone', "UTC"), source_tz="UTC") }} as updated_timestamp,
        {{ shopify_source.fivetran_convert_timezone(column='cast(_fivetran_synced as ' ~ dbt.type_timestamp() ~ ')', target_tz=var('shopify_timezone', "UTC"), source_tz="UTC") }} as _fivetran_synced,
        source_relation

        {{ fivetran_utils.fill_pass_through_columns('product_variant_pass_through_columns') }}

    from fields
)

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__order_.name: stg_shopify__order_line
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__order_.description: Each record represents a line item from an order in Shopify.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

fulfillable_quantity.name: fulfillable_quantity
fulfillable_quantity.description: The amount available to fulfill, calculated as follows: quantity - max(refunded_quantity, fulfilled_quantity) - pending_fulfilled_quantity - open_fulfilled_quantity

fulfillment_status.name: fulfillment_status
fulfillment_status.description: How far along an order is in terms line items fulfilled.

is_gift_card.name: is_gift_card
is_gift_card.description: Whether the item is a gift card. If true, then the item is not taxed or considered for shipping charges.

grams.name: grams
grams.description: The weight of the item in grams.

order_line_id.name: order_line_id
order_line_id.description: The ID of the line item.

name.name: name
name.description: The name of the product variant.

order_id.name: order_id
order_id.description: The ID of the related order.

price.name: price
price.description: The price of the item before discounts have been applied in the shop currency.

product_id.name: product_id
product_id.description: The ID of the product that the line item belongs to. Can be null if the original product associated with the order is deleted at a later date.

quantity.name: quantity
quantity.description: The number of items that were purchased.

title.name: title
title.description: The title of the product.

total_discount.name: total_discount
total_discount.description: The total amount of the discount allocated to the line item in the shop currency.

variant_id.name: variant_id
variant_id.description: The ID of the product variant.

vendor.name: vendor
vendor.description: The name of the item's supplier.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

index.name: index
index.description: Index of the order line.

pre_tax_price.name: pre_tax_price
pre_tax_price.description: The pre tax price of the line item in shop currency.

pre_tax_price_set.name: pre_tax_price_set
pre_tax_price_set.description: The pre tax price of the line item in shop currency and presentment currency.

price_set.name: price_set
price_set.description: The price of the line item in shop and presentment currencies.

tax_code.name: tax_code
tax_code.description: Tax code applied to the line item. As multiple taxes can apply to a line item, we recommend referring to `stg_shopify__tax_line`.

total_discount_set.name: total_discount_set
total_discount_set.description: The total amount allocated to the line item in the presentment currency.

variant_title.name: variant_title
variant_title.description: The title of the product variant.

variant_inventory_management.name: variant_inventory_management
variant_inventory_management.description: The fulfillment service that tracks the number of items in stock for the product variant.

title.name: title

status.name: status

applies_once_per_customer.name: applies_once_per_customer
applies_once_per_customer.description: Boolean representing whether the discount code is limited to one use per customer.

usage_limit.name: usage_limit

usage_count.name: usage_count

codes_count.name: codes_count

codes_precision.name: codes_precision
codes_precision.description: Indicates the precision or type of generated codes (e.g., exact vs. bulk).

combines_with_order_discounts.name: combines_with_order_discounts
combines_with_order_discounts.description: Whether this discount can be combined with other order-level discounts.

combines_with_product_discounts.name: combines_with_product_discounts
combines_with_product_discounts.description: Whether this discount can be combined with product-level discounts.

combines_with_shipping_discounts.name: combines_with_shipping_discounts
combines_with_shipping_discounts.description: Whether this discount can be combined with shipping discounts.

customer_selection_all_customers.name: customer_selection_all_customers

total_sales_amount.name: total_sales_amount

created_at.name: created_at
created_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the discount code was created.

updated_at.name: updated_at
updated_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the discount code was last updated.

starts_at.name: starts_at

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__fulfil.name: stg_shopify__fulfillment_event
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__fulfil.description: The FulfillmentEvent resource represents tracking events that belong to a fulfillment of one or more items in an order.  Fulfillment events are displayed on the order status page to update customers on the status of their shipment.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

address_1.name: address_1
address_1.description: The street address where the fulfillment event occurred.

city.name: city
city.description: The city where the fulfillment event occurred.

country.name: country
country.description: The country where the fulfillment event occurred.

created_at.name: created_at
created_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the fulfillment event was created.

estimated_delivery_at.name: estimated_delivery_at
estimated_delivery_at.description: The estimated delivery date based on the fulfillment's tracking number, as long as it's provided by one of the following carriers: USPS, FedEx, UPS, or Canada Post (Canada only).  Value is `null` if no tracking number is available or if the tracking number is from an unsupported carrier. This property is available only when carrier calculated rates are in use.

fulfillment_id.name: fulfillment_id
fulfillment_id.description: An ID for the fulfillment that's associated with the fulfillment event.

happened_at.name: happened_at
happened_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the fulfillment event occurred.

fulfillment_event_id.name: fulfillment_event_id
fulfillment_event_id.description: An ID for the fulfillment event.

latitude.name: latitude
latitude.description: A geographic coordinate specifying the latitude of the fulfillment event.

longitude.name: longitude
longitude.description: A geographic coordinate specifying the longitude of the fulfillment event.

message.name: message
message.description: An arbitrary message describing the status. Can be provided by a shipping carrier.

order_id.name: order_id
order_id.description: The ID of the order that's associated with the fulfillment event.

province.name: province
province.description: The province where the fulfillment event occurred.

shop_id.name: shop_id
shop_id.description: An ID for the shop that's associated with the fulfillment event.

status.name: status
status.description: The status of the fulfillment event. Valid values: - label_printed: A label for the shipment was purchased and printed. - label_purchased: A label for the shipment was purchased, but not printed. - attempted_delivery: Delivery of the shipment was attempted, but unable to be completed. - ready_for_pickup: The shipment is ready for pickup at a shipping depot. - picked_up: The fulfillment was successfully picked up. - confirmed: The carrier is aware of the shipment, but hasn't received it yet. - in_transit: The shipment is being transported between shipping facilities on the way to its destination. - out_for_delivery: The shipment is being delivered to its final destination. - delivered: The shipment was successfully delivered. - failure: Something went wrong when pulling tracking information for the shipment, such as the tracking number was invalid or the shipment was canceled.

updated_at.name: updated_at
updated_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the fulfillment event was updated.

zip.name: zip
zip.description: The zip code of the location where the fulfillment event occurred.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

By default, existing products are set to active. - archived: The product is no longer being sold and isn't available to customers on sales channels and apps. - draft: The product isn't ready to sell and is unavailable to customers on sales channels and apps. By default, duplicated and unarchived products are set to draft.

shipping_address_longitude.description: The longitude of the shipping address.

shipping_address_name.name: shipping_address_name
shipping_address_name.description: The full name of the person associated with the shipping address.

shipping_address_phone.name: shipping_address_phone

shipping_address_province.name: shipping_address_province
shipping_address_province.description: The name of the state or province of the shipping address.

shipping_address_province_code.name: shipping_address_province_code
shipping_address_province_code.description: The two-letter abbreviation of the state or province of the shipping address.

shipping_address_zip.name: shipping_address_zip
shipping_address_zip.description: The zip or postal code of the shipping address.

source_name.name: source_name
source_name.description: Where the checkout originated. Valid values include `web`, `pos`, `iphone`, `android`.

subtotal_price.name: subtotal_price
subtotal_price.description: The price of the checkout in _presentment_ (customer) currency before shipping and taxes.

has_taxes_included.name: has_taxes_included
has_taxes_included.description: Boolean representing whether taxes are included in the price.

token.name: token
token.description: A unique ID for a checkout.

total_discounts.name: total_discounts
total_discounts.description: The total amount of discounts to be applied in presentment currency.

total_duties.name: total_duties
total_duties.description: The total duties of the checkout in presentment currency.

total_line_items_price.name: total_line_items_price
total_line_items_price.description: The sum of the prices of all line items in the checkout in _presentment_ (customer) currency.

total_price.name: total_price
total_price.description: The sum of line item prices, all discounts, shipping costs, and taxes for the checkout in _presentment_ (customer) currency.

total_tax.name: total_tax
total_tax.description: The sum of all the taxes applied to the checkout in _presentment_ (customer) currency.

total_weight.name: total_weight
total_weight.description: The sum of all the weights in grams of the line items in the checkout.

updated_at.name: updated_at
updated_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the checkout was last modified.

user_id.name: user_id
user_id.description: The ID of the user who created the checkout.

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__discou.name: stg_shopify__discount_code_app
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify__discou.description: Table storing metadata for discount codes created through third-party apps in Shopify.

discount_code_id.name: discount_code_id
discount_code_id.description: The unique ID for the discount code.

title.name: title
title.description: The display name for the discount code.

status.name: status
status.description: The status of the discount code (e.g., `enabled`, `disabled`, `expired`).

applies_once_per_customer.name: applies_once_per_customer
applies_once_per_customer.description: Boolean representing whether the discount code is limited to one use per customer.

usage_limit.name: usage_limit
usage_limit.description: The total number of times the discount code can be used.

usage_count.name: usage_count
usage_count.description: The number of times the discount code has been used.

codes_count.name: codes_count
codes_count.description: The total number of redeemable codes generated for this discount.

codes_precision.name: codes_precision
codes_precision.description: Indicates the precision or type of generated codes (e.g., exact vs. bulk).

combines_with_order_discounts.name: combines_with_order_discounts
combines_with_order_discounts.description: Whether this discount can be combined with other order-level discounts.

combines_with_product_discounts.name: combines_with_product_discounts
combines_with_product_discounts.description: Whether this discount can be combined with product-level discounts.

combines_with_shipping_discounts.name: combines_with_shipping_discounts
combines_with_shipping_discounts.description: Whether this discount can be combined with shipping discounts.

customer_selection_all_customers.name: customer_selection_all_customers
customer_selection_all_customers.description: Boolean indicating whether the discount is available to all customers.

recurring_cycle_limit.name: recurring_cycle_limit
recurring_cycle_limit.description: The number of billing cycles this discount applies to (for subscription products).

total_sales_amount.name: total_sales_amount
total_sales_amount.description: The total sales amount that resulted from the usage of this discount.

created_at.name: created_at
created_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the discount code was created.

updated_at.name: updated_at
updated_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the discount code was last updated.

starts_at.name: starts_at
starts_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the discount code becomes active.

ends_at.name: ends_at
ends_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the discount code expires.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__or.name: stg_shopify_gql__order_line
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__or.description: Each record represents a line item from an order in Shopify.

order_line_id.name: order_line_id
order_line_id.description: The ID of the line item.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

fulfillment_status.name: fulfillment_status
fulfillment_status.description: How far along an order is in terms line items fulfilled.

is_gift_card.name: is_gift_card
is_gift_card.description: Whether the item is a gift card. If true, then the item is not taxed or considered for shipping charges.

name.name: name
name.description: The name of the product variant.

order_id.name: order_id
order_id.description: The ID of the related order.

price_pres_amount.name: price_pres_amount
price_pres_amount.description: The total price of the line item when the order was created, in *presentment* currency. This value doesn't include discounts.

price_pres_currency_code.name: price_pres_currency_code
price_pres_currency_code.description: The three-letter code (ISO 4217 format) for the presentment currency used to display the total price.

price_shop_amount.name: price_shop_amount
price_shop_amount.description: The total price of the line item when the order was created, in *shop* currency. This value doesn't include discounts.

price_shop_currency_code.name: price_shop_currency_code
price_shop_currency_code.description: The three-letter code (ISO 4217 format) for the shop currency used to display the total price.

product_id.name: product_id
product_id.description: The ID of the product that the line item belongs to. Can be null if the original product associated with the order is deleted at a later date.

quantity.name: quantity
quantity.description: The number of items that were purchased.

title.name: title
title.description: The title of the product.

total_discount_shop_amount.name: total_discount_shop_amount
total_discount_shop_amount.description: The total discount allocated to the line item in *shop* currency, including the total allocated to refunded and removed quantities. This value doesn't include order-level discounts.

total_discount_pres_amount.name: total_discount_pres_amount
total_discount_pres_amount.description: The total discount allocated to the line item in *presentment* currency, including the total allocated to refunded and removed quantities. This value doesn't include order-level discounts.

total_discount_shop_currency_code.name: total_discount_shop_currency_code
total_discount_shop_currency_code.description: The three-letter code (ISO å4217 format) for the shop currency used to display the total discount.

total_discount_pres_currency_code.name: total_discount_pres_currency_code
total_discount_pres_currency_code.description: The three-letter code (ISO 4217 format) for the currency currency used to display the total discount.

variant_id.name: variant_id
variant_id.description: The ID of the product variant.

vendor.name: vendor
vendor.description: The name of the item's supplier.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

index.name: index
index.description: Index of the order line.

variant_title.name: variant_title
variant_title.description: The title of the product variant.

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__or.raw_code:
{{ config(enabled=var('shopify_api', 'rest') == var('shopify_api_override','graphql')) }}

with base as (

    select * 
    from {{ ref('stg_shopify_gql__order_line_tmp') }}
),

fields as (

    select
        {{
            fivetran_utils.fill_staging_columns(
                source_columns=adapter.get_columns_in_relation(ref('stg_shopify_gql__order_line_tmp')),
                staging_columns=get_graphql_order_line_columns()
            )
        }}
        {{ fivetran_utils.source_relation(
            union_schema_variable='shopify_union_schemas', 
            union_database_variable='shopify_union_databases') 
        }}
    from base
),

final as (
    
    select 
        id as order_line_id,
        row_number() over(partition by order_id, source_relation order by id asc) as index,
        name,
        order_id,
        case 
            when unfulfilled_quantity = 0 then 'fulfilled'
            when unfulfilled_quantity > 0 and unfulfilled_quantity < quantity then 'partial'
            when unfulfilled_quantity = quantity then 'unfulfilled'
            else null 
        end as fulfillment_status,
        is_gift_card,
        original_total_set_pres_amount as price_pres_amount,
        original_total_set_pres_currency_code as price_pres_currency_code,
        original_total_set_shop_amount as price_shop_amount,
        original_total_set_shop_currency_code as price_shop_currency_code,
        product_id,
        quantity,
        requires_shipping as is_shipping_required,
        sku,
        taxable as is_taxable,
        title,
        total_discount_set_pres_amount as total_discount_pres_amount,
        total_discount_set_pres_currency_code as total_discount_pres_currency_code,
        total_discount_set_shop_amount as total_discount_shop_amount,
        total_discount_set_shop_currency_code as total_discount_shop_currency_code,
        variant_id,
        variant_title,
        vendor,
        {{ shopify_source.fivetran_convert_timezone(column='cast(_fivetran_synced as ' ~ dbt.type_timestamp() ~ ')', target_tz=var('shopify_timezone', "UTC"), source_tz="UTC") }} as _fivetran_synced,
        source_relation,
