model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__in.name: stg_shopify_gql__inventory_item
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__in.description: An inventory item represents a physical good. It holds essential information about the physical good, including its SKU and whether its inventory is tracked. There is a 1:1 relationship between a product variant and an inventory item.

inventory_item_id.name: inventory_item_id
inventory_item_id.description: The ID of the inventory item.

is_deleted.name: is_deleted
is_deleted.description: Boolean representing whether the record was soft-deleted in Shopify.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

country_code_of_origin.name: country_code_of_origin
country_code_of_origin.description: The country code (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) of where the item came from.

created_at.name: created_at
created_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the inventory item was created.

province_code_of_origin.name: province_code_of_origin
province_code_of_origin.description: The province code (ISO 3166-2 alpha-2) of where the item came from. The province code is only used if the shipping provider for the inventory item is Canada Post.

is_shipping_required.name: is_shipping_required
is_shipping_required.description: Boolean representing whether a customer needs to provide a shipping address when placing an order containing the inventory item.

sku.name: sku
sku.description: The unique SKU (stock keeping unit) of the inventory item.

is_inventory_quantity_tracked.name: is_inventory_quantity_tracked
is_inventory_quantity_tracked.description: Boolean representing whether inventory levels are tracked for the item. If true, then the inventory quantity changes are tracked by Shopify.

updated_at.name: updated_at
updated_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the inventory item was last modified.

duplicate_sku_count.name: duplicate_sku_count
duplicate_sku_count.description: The number of inventory items that share the same SKU with this item.

harmonized_system_code.name: harmonized_system_code
harmonized_system_code.description: The harmonized system code of the item.

inventory_history_url.name: inventory_history_url
inventory_history_url.description: The URL that points to the inventory history for the item.

legacy_resource_id.name: legacy_resource_id
legacy_resource_id.description: The ID of the corresponding resource in the REST Admin API.

measurement_id.name: measurement_id
measurement_id.description: The unique identifier for the inventory item's measurement.

measurement_weight_value.name: measurement_weight_value
measurement_weight_value.description: The weight value of the inventory item's measurement.

measurement_weight_unit.name: measurement_weight_unit
measurement_weight_unit.description: The unit of measurement for the inventory item's weight.

tracked_editable_reason.name: tracked_editable_reason
tracked_editable_reason.description: Provides the reason why the 'tracked' field for the inventory item is locked from editing.

unit_cost_amount.name: unit_cost_amount
unit_cost_amount.description: Decimal money amount of the unit cost associated with the inventory item.

unit_cost_currency_code.name: unit_cost_currency_code
unit_cost_currency_code.description: Currency of the unit cost associated with the inventory item.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

is_tracked_editable_locked.name: is_tracked_editable_locked
is_tracked_editable_locked.description: Indicates whether the 'tracked' field for the inventory item is locked from editing.

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__fu.name: stg_shopify_gql__fulfillment_order_line_item
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__fu.description: Links a fulfillment order to specific items that require fulfillment. Contains detailed product information, quantity tracking, variant metadata, and shipping requirements. This is a core entity for determining which products and how many units are involved in a given fulfillment process.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

fulfillment_order_line_item_id.name: fulfillment_order_line_item_id
fulfillment_order_line_item_id.description: A globally unique identifier for this fulfillment order line item.

fulfillment_order_id.name: fulfillment_order_id
fulfillment_order_id.description: The identifier of the fulfillment order that this line item is associated with.

image_alt_text.name: image_alt_text
image_alt_text.description: Alt text describing the image associated with the line item's variant.

image_height.name: image_height
image_height.description: The height in pixels of the variant image, if hosted by Shopify.

image_id.name: image_id
image_id.description: The unique identifier for the variant image.

image_url.name: image_url
image_url.description: The url of the variant image used in this fulfillment line item.

image_width.name: image_width
image_width.description: The width in pixels of the variant image, if hosted by Shopify.

inventory_item_id.name: inventory_item_id
inventory_item_id.description: The identifier of the inventory item being fulfilled.

order_line_item_id.name: order_line_item_id
order_line_item_id.description: The identifier of the original order line item linked to this fulfillment.

product_title.name: product_title
product_title.description: The title of the product at the time of order creation.

product_variant_id.name: product_variant_id
product_variant_id.description: The identifier of the product variant associated with this fulfillment item.

remaining_quantity.name: remaining_quantity
remaining_quantity.description: The number of units remaining to be fulfilled.

requires_shipping.name: requires_shipping
requires_shipping.description: Indicates whether physical shipping is required for this item.

sku.name: sku
sku.description: The SKU of the product variant.

total_quantity.name: total_quantity
total_quantity.description: The total number of units allocated to this fulfillment.

variant_title.name: variant_title
variant_title.description: The title of the product variant at the time of order creation.

vendor.name: vendor
vendor.description: The vendor of the product variant.

weight_unit.name: weight_unit
weight_unit.description: The unit of measurement for the weight of a single item (e.g., grams, ounces).

weight_value.name: weight_value
weight_value.description: The numeric weight of a single unit of the line item using the specified `weight_unit`.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__fu.name: stg_shopify_gql__fulfillment
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__fu.description: A fulfillment order represents a group of one or more items in an order that will be fulfilled from the same location.  A fulfillment represents work that is completed as part of a fulfillment order and can include one or more items.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

created_at.name: created_at
created_at.description: The date and time when the fulfillment was created. The API returns this value in ISO 8601 format.

location_id.name: location_id
location_id.description: The unique identifier of the location that the fulfillment was processed at.

name.name: name
name.description: The uniquely identifying fulfillment name, consisting of two parts separated by a .. The first part represents the order name and the second part represents the fulfillment number.  The fulfillment number automatically increments depending on how many fulfillments are in an order (e.g. #1001.1, #1001.2).

order_id.name: order_id
order_id.description: The unique numeric identifier for the order.

service.name: service
service.description: The fulfillment service associated with the fulfillment.

shipment_status.name: shipment_status
shipment_status.description: The current shipment status of the fulfillment. Valid values include: - label_printed: A label for the shipment was purchased and printed. - label_purchased: A label for the shipment was purchased, but not printed. - attempted_delivery: Delivery of the shipment was attempted, but unable to be completed. - ready_for_pickup: The shipment is ready for pickup at a shipping depot. - confirmed: The carrier is aware of the shipment, but hasn't received it yet. - in_transit: The shipment is being transported between shipping facilities on the way to its destination. - out_for_delivery: The shipment is being delivered to its final destination. - delivered: The shipment was successfully delivered. - failure: Something went wrong when pulling tracking information for the shipment, such as the tracking number was invalid or the shipment was canceled.

status.name: status
status.description: The status of the fulfillment. Valid values include: - pending: Shopify has created the fulfillment and is waiting for the third-party fulfillment service to transition it to 'open' or 'success'. - open: The fulfillment has been acknowledged by the service and is in processing. - success: The fulfillment was successful. - cancelled: The fulfillment was cancelled. - error: There was an error with the fulfillment request. - failure: The fulfillment request failed.

updated_at.name: updated_at
updated_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the fulfillment was last modified.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

is_deleted.name: is_deleted

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced

has_checkout_api_supported.description: Boolean representing whether the shop is capable of accepting payments directly through the Checkout API.

country.name: country
country.description: The shop's country. In most cases, this value matches the country_code.

country_code.name: country_code
country_code.description: The two-letter country code corresponding to the shop's country.

created_at.name: created_at
created_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601) when the shop was created.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: The three-letter code (ISO 4217 format) for the shop's default currency.

customer_email.description: The contact email used for communication between the shop owner and the customer.

email.name: email
email.description: The contact email used for communication between Shopify and the shop owner.

enabled_presentment_currencies.description: An array of of enabled currencies (ISO 4217 format) that the shop accepts. Merchants can enable currencies from their Shopify Payments settings in the Shopify Admin.

has_storefront.name: has_storefront
has_storefront.description: Boolean representing whether this shop has an online store.

iana_timezone.name: iana_timezone
iana_timezone.description: The name of the timezone assigned by the [IANA](https://www.iana.org/time-zones).

shop_id.description: The ID for the shop. A 64-bit unsigned integer.

latitude.name: latitude
latitude.description: The latitude of the shop's location.

longitude.name: longitude
longitude.description: The longitude of the shop's location.

money_format.name: money_format
money_format.description: A string representing the way currency is formatted when the currency isn't specified.

money_in_emails_format.name: money_in_emails_format
money_in_emails_format.description: A string representing the way currency is formatted in email notifications when the currency isn't specified.

money_with_currency_format.name: money_with_currency_format
money_with_currency_format.description: A string representing the way currency is formatted when the currency is specified.

money_with_currency_in_emails_format.name: money_with_currency_in_emails_format
money_with_currency_in_emails_format.description: A string representing the way currency is formatted in email notifications when the currency is specified.

name.name: name
name.description: The name of the shop.

is_password_enabled.name: is_password_enabled
is_password_enabled.description: Boolean representing whether the password protection page is enabled on the shop's online store.

phone.name: phone
phone.description: The contact phone number for the shop.

plan_display_name.name: plan_display_name
plan_display_name.description: The display name of the Shopify plan the shop is on.

primary_locale.name: primary_locale
primary_locale.description: The shop's primary locale, as configured in the language settings of the shop's theme.

province.name: province
province.description: The shop's normalized province or state name.

province_code.name: province_code
province_code.description: The two- or three-letter code for the shop's province or state.

is_setup_required.name: is_setup_required
is_setup_required.description: Boolean representing whether the shop has any outstanding setup steps.

shop_owner.name: shop_owner
shop_owner.description: The username of the shop owner.

has_shipping_taxes.name: has_shipping_taxes
has_shipping_taxes.description: Boolean representing whether taxes are charged for shipping. Valid values are true or false.

has_taxes_included_in_price.name: has_taxes_included_in_price
has_taxes_included_in_price.description: Boolean representing whether applicable taxes are included in product prices. Valid values are true or null.

timezone_offset_minutes.name: timezone_offset_minutes
timezone_offset_minutes.description: The shop's time zone offset expressed as a number of minutes.

updated_at.name: updated_at
updated_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601) when the shop was last updated.

weight_unit.name: weight_unit
weight_unit.description: The default unit of weight measurement for the shop.

zip.name: zip
zip.description: The shop's zip or postal code.

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__lo.description: A location represents a geographical location where your stores, pop-up stores, headquarters, and warehouses exist.

location_id.name: location_id
location_id.description: The ID of the location.

is_deleted.name: is_deleted
is_deleted.description: Boolean representing whether the record was soft-deleted in Shopify.

is_active.description: Boolean representing whether the location is active. If true, then the location can be used to sell products, stock inventory, and fulfill orders.

address_2.name: address_2

city.name: city

created_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the location was created.

is_legacy.name: is_legacy

province.name: province

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__tr.description: Each record represents a transaction in Shopify.

order_id.name: order_id
order_id.description: The ID for the order that the transaction is associated with.

refund_id.name: refund_id
refund_id.description: The ID associated with a refund in the refund table.

amount_pres.name: amount_pres
amount_pres.description: The amount of the transaction in the customer currency.

amount_pres_currency_code.name: amount_pres_currency_code
amount_pres_currency_code.description: The three letter currency code of the customer currency.

amount_shop.name: amount_shop
amount_shop.description: The amount of the transaction in the shop currency.

amount_shop_currency_code.name: amount_shop_currency_code
amount_shop_currency_code.description: The three letter currency code of the shop's transaction currency.

authorization_code.name: authorization_code
authorization_code.description: The authorization code associated with the transaction.

created_timestamp.name: created_timestamp
created_timestamp.description: The date and time when the transaction was created.

processed_timestamp.name: processed_timestamp
processed_timestamp.description: The date and time when a transaction was processed.

gateway.name: gateway
gateway.description: The name of the gateway the transaction was issued through.

parent_id.name: parent_id
parent_id.description: The ID of an associated transaction.

payment_avs_result_code.name: payment_avs_result_code
payment_avs_result_code.description: The response code from the address verification system.

payment_credit_card_bin.name: payment_credit_card_bin
payment_credit_card_bin.description: The issuer identification number (IIN), formerly known as bank identification number (BIN) of the customer's credit card.

payment_cvv_result_code.name: payment_cvv_result_code
payment_cvv_result_code.description: The response code from the credit card company indicating whether the customer entered the card security code, or card verification value, correctly.

payment_credit_card_number.name: payment_credit_card_number
payment_credit_card_number.description: The customer's credit card number, with most of the leading digits redacted.

payment_credit_card_company.name: payment_credit_card_company
payment_credit_card_company.description: The name of the company that issued the customer's credit card.

receipt.name: receipt
receipt.description: A transaction receipt attached to the transaction by the gateway.

error_code.name: error_code
error_code.description: A standardized error code, independent of the payment provider.

status.name: status
status.description: The status of the transaction.

user_id.name: user_id
user_id.description: The ID for the user who was logged into the Shopify POS device when the order was processed, if applicable.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

authorization_expires_at.name: authorization_expires_at
authorization_expires_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the Shopify Payments authorization expires.

currency_exchange_adjustment.name: currency_exchange_adjustment
currency_exchange_adjustment.description: The difference between the amounts on the associated transaction and the parent transaction.

currency_exchange_original_amount.name: currency_exchange_original_amount
currency_exchange_original_amount.description: The amount of the parent transaction in the shop currency.

currency_exchange_final_amount.name: currency_exchange_final_amount
currency_exchange_final_amount.description: The amount of the associated transaction in the shop currency.

        source_relation,
        {{ dbt_utils.generate_surrogate_key(['id', 'source_relation']) }} as unique_key

        {{ fivetran_utils.fill_pass_through_columns('transaction_pass_through_columns') }}

    from fields
    where not coalesce(test, false)
)

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__co.name: stg_shopify_gql__collection
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__co.description: A collection is a grouping of products that merchants can create to make their stores easier to browse. Merchants can create collections by selecting products individually or by defining rules that automatically determine whether products are included (aka a "smart collection").

is_deleted.name: is_deleted
is_deleted.description: Boolean representing whether the record was soft-deleted in Shopify.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

rule_logic.name: rule_logic
rule_logic.description: Whether the `rules` are disjunctive (logical `OR`) or conjunctive (logical `AND`)

handle.name: handle
handle.description: A unique, human-readable string for the collection automatically generated from its title. This is used in themes by the Liquid templating language to refer to the collection.

sort_order.name: sort_order
sort_order.description: The order of the products in the collection. Valid values incline - `alpha-asc`: The products are sorted alphabetically from A to Z. - `alpha-des`: The products are sorted alphabetically from Z to A. - `best-selling`: The products are sorted by number of sales. - `created`: The products are sorted by the date they were created, from oldest to newest. - `created-desc`: The products are sorted by the date they were created, from newest to oldest. - `manual`: The products are manually sorted by the shop owner. - `price-asc`: The products are sorted by price from lowest to highest. - `price-desc`: The products are sorted by price from highest to lowest.

title.name: title
title.description: The name of the collection.

updated_at.name: updated_at
updated_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the collection was last modified.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__di.name: stg_shopify_gql__discount_application
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__di.description: Table storing discount applications, which define how discounts were applied at the order level.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

allocation_method.name: allocation_method
allocation_method.description: The method by which the discount is allocated. Valid values include `each` (applies the discount to each eligible item) and `across` (spreads the discount value across eligible items).

index.name: index
index.description: The index of the discount application on the order.

order_id.name: order_id
order_id.description: The ID of the order to which the discount was applied.

target_selection.name: target_selection
target_selection.description: Indicates whether the discount applies to all line items (`all`) or only those that are specifically entitled (`entitled`).

target_type.name: target_type
target_type.description: The type of target this discount applies to (e.g., `line_item` or `shipping_line`).

value_amount.name: value_amount
value_amount.description: The numerical value of the discount application. A monetary value in decimal format, allowing for precise representation of cents or fractional currency.

value_currency_code.name: value_currency_code
value_currency_code.description: The three-letter currency code for the discount that represents a world currency used in a store.

value_percentage.name: value_percentage
value_percentage.description: The percentage discount value that is applied to a line, a number ranging between -100 (free) and 0 (no discount)

value_type.name: value_type
value_type.description: Indicates whether the discount value is a `percentage` or `fixed_amount`. If `target_type` is `shipping_line`, only `percentage` is accepted.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

code.name: code
code.description: The discount code applied, if applicable.

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__di.description: Table storing metadata about basic discount codes created by merchants.

discount_code_id.name: discount_code_id
discount_code_id.description: The unique ID for the discount code.

title.description: The display name for the discount code.

status.name: status
status.description: The status of the discount code (e.g., `enabled`, `disabled`, `expired`).

applies_once_per_customer.name: applies_once_per_customer
applies_once_per_customer.description: Boolean representing whether the discount code is limited to one use per customer.

usage_limit.name: usage_limit
usage_limit.description: The total number of times the discount code can be used.

usage_count.name: usage_count
usage_count.description: The number of times the discount code has been used.

codes_count.name: codes_count
codes_count.description: The total number of redeemable codes generated for this discount.

codes_precision.name: codes_precision
codes_precision.description: Indicates the precision or type of generated codes (e.g., exact vs. bulk).

combines_with_order_discounts.name: combines_with_order_discounts
combines_with_order_discounts.description: Whether this discount can be combined with other order-level discounts.

combines_with_product_discounts.name: combines_with_product_discounts
combines_with_product_discounts.description: Whether this discount can be combined with product-level discounts.

combines_with_shipping_discounts.name: combines_with_shipping_discounts
combines_with_shipping_discounts.description: Whether this discount can be combined with shipping discounts.

customer_selection_all_customers.name: customer_selection_all_customers
customer_selection_all_customers.description: Boolean indicating whether the discount is available to all customers.

recurring_cycle_limit.name: recurring_cycle_limit
recurring_cycle_limit.description: The number of billing cycles this discount applies to (for subscription products).

total_sales_amount.name: total_sales_amount
total_sales_amount.description: The total sales amount that resulted from the usage of this discount.

created_at.name: created_at
created_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the discount code was created.

updated_at.name: updated_at
updated_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the discount code was last updated.

starts_at.name: starts_at
starts_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the discount code becomes active.

ends_at.name: ends_at
ends_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the discount code expires.

source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__te.description: Each tender transaction represents money passing between the merchant and a customer. A tender transaction with a positive amount  represents a transaction where the customer paid money to the merchant. A negative amount represents a transaction where the  merchant refunded money back to the customer. Tender transactions represent transactions that modify the shop's balance.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

amount.name: amount
amount.description: The amount of the tender transaction in the shop's currency.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: The three-letter code (ISO 4217 format) for the currency used for the tender transaction.

order_id.name: order_id
order_id.description: The ID of the order that the tender transaction belongs to.

payment_method.name: payment_method
payment_method.description: Information about the payment method used for this transaction. Valid values include: - credit_card - cash - android_pay - apple_pay - google_pay - samsung_pay - shopify_pay - amazon - klarna - paypal - unknown - other

processed_at.name: processed_at
processed_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the tender transaction was processed.

remote_reference.name: remote_reference
remote_reference.description: The remote (gateway) reference associated with the tender.

user_id.name: user_id
user_id.description: The ID of the user logged into the Shopify POS device that processed the tender transaction, if applicable.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

marketing_opt_in_level.description: The marketing subscription opt-in level, as described in the M3AAWG Sender Best Common Practices, that the customer gave when they consented to receive marketing material by email.

marketing_consent_updated_at.description: The date and time when the customer consented to receive marketing material by email. If no date is provided, then the date and time when the consent information was sent is used.

created_timestamp.name: created_timestamp
created_timestamp.description: The date and time when the customer was created.

email.name: email
email.description: The unique email address of the customer. Attempting to assign the same email address to multiple customers returns an error.

orders_count.name: orders_count
orders_count.description: The number of orders associated with this customer.

phone.name: phone
phone.description: The unique phone number (E.164 format) for this customer. Attempting to assign the same phone number to multiple customers returns an error.

account_state.name: account_state
account_state.description: The state of the customer's account with a shop.

is_tax_exempt.name: is_tax_exempt
is_tax_exempt.description: Whether the customer is exempt from paying taxes on their order. If true, then taxes won't be applied to an order at checkout. If false, then taxes will be applied at checkout.

total_spent.name: total_spent
total_spent.description: The total amount of money that the customer has spent across their order history.

updated_timestamp.name: updated_timestamp
updated_timestamp.description: The date and time when the customer information was last updated.

is_verified_email.name: is_verified_email
is_verified_email.description: Whether the customer has verified their email address.

currency.name: currency
currency.description: The three-letter code (ISO 4217 format) for the currency that the customer used when they paid for their last order. Defaults to the shop currency. Returns the shop currency for test orders.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__me.name: stg_shopify_gql__metafield
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__me.description: Metafields are a flexible way to attach additional information to a Shopify resource (e.g. Product, Collection, etc.). Some examples of data stored using metafields include specifications, size charts,  downloadable documents, release dates, images, or part numbers. Metafields are identified by an owner resource, a namespace, and a key and they store a value along with type information for that context.

metafield_id.name: metafield_id
metafield_id.description: The unique ID of the metafield.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

created_at.name: created_at
created_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the metafield was created.

description.name: description
description.description: A description of the information that the metafield contains.

key.name: key
key.description: The key of the metafield. Keys can be up to 64 characters long and can contain alphanumeric characters, hyphens, underscores, and periods.

namespace.name: namespace
namespace.description: A container for a group of metafields. Grouping metafields within a namespace prevents your metafields from conflicting with other metafields with the same key name. Must have between 3-255 characters.

owner_resource_id.name: owner_resource_id
owner_resource_id.description: The unique ID of the resource that the metafield is attached to.

owner_resource.name: owner_resource
owner_resource.description: The type of resource (table) that the metafield is attached to.

updated_at.name: updated_at
updated_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the metafield was last updated.

value.name: value
value.description: The data to store in the metafield. The value is always stored as a string, regardless of the metafield's type.

metafield_reference.name: metafield_reference
metafield_reference.description: Combination of the namespace and key columns. This field is key for metafield mapping in downstream models.

is_most_recent_record.name: is_most_recent_record
is_most_recent_record.description: Boolean indicating the most up to date record identified by the most recent updated_at field.

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__fu.description: The FulfillmentEvent resource represents tracking events that belong to a fulfillment of one or more items in an order.  Fulfillment events are displayed on the order status page to update customers on the status of their shipment.

city.description: The city where the fulfillment event occurred.

country.name: country
country.description: The country where the fulfillment event occurred.

created_at.name: created_at
created_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the fulfillment event was created.

estimated_delivery_at.name: estimated_delivery_at
estimated_delivery_at.description: The estimated delivery date based on the fulfillment's tracking number, as long as it's provided by one of the following carriers: USPS, FedEx, UPS, or Canada Post (Canada only).  Value is `null` if no tracking number is available or if the tracking number is from an unsupported carrier. This property is available only when carrier calculated rates are in use.

fulfillment_id.description: An ID for the fulfillment that's associated with the fulfillment event.

happened_at.name: happened_at
happened_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the fulfillment event occurred.

fulfillment_event_id.name: fulfillment_event_id
fulfillment_event_id.description: An ID for the fulfillment event.

latitude.name: latitude

longitude.name: longitude
longitude.description: A geographic coordinate specifying the longitude of the fulfillment event.

message.name: message
message.description: An arbitrary message describing the status. Can be provided by a shipping carrier.

province.name: province

status.name: status
status.description: The status of the fulfillment event. Valid values: - label_printed: A label for the shipment was purchased and printed. - label_purchased: A label for the shipment was purchased, but not printed. - attempted_delivery: Delivery of the shipment was attempted, but unable to be completed. - ready_for_pickup: The shipment is ready for pickup at a shipping depot. - picked_up: The fulfillment was successfully picked up. - confirmed: The carrier is aware of the shipment, but hasn't received it yet. - in_transit: The shipment is being transported between shipping facilities on the way to its destination. - out_for_delivery: The shipment is being delivered to its final destination. - delivered: The shipment was successfully delivered. - failure: Something went wrong when pulling tracking information for the shipment, such as the tracking number was invalid or the shipment was canceled.

zip.name: zip
zip.description: The zip code of the location where the fulfillment event occurred.

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__di.name: stg_shopify_gql__discount_redeem_code
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__di.description: Table storing individual redeem codes that customers can use at checkout to receive a discount. Each redeem code is tied to a parent discount and may be created by an app or manually.

discount_code_id.name: discount_code_id
discount_code_id.description: The unique ID of the redeem code.

async_usage_count.name: async_usage_count
async_usage_count.description: The number of times that the redeem code has been used. This is updated asynchronously and may differ from real-time usage.

code.name: code
code.description: The redeemable code that a customer can enter at checkout (e.g., `SUMMER20`).

created_by_description.name: created_by_description
created_by_description.description: A descriptive label of the app or user who created the redeem code.

created_by_id.name: created_by_id
created_by_id.description: The internal ID of the app or user that created the redeem code.

created_by_title.name: created_by_title
created_by_title.description: The name or title of the creator of the redeem code (typically an app name).

discount_id.name: discount_id
discount_id.description: The unique ID of the parent discount associated with this redeem code.

discount_type.name: discount_type
discount_type.description: The type of discount the redeem code is associated with (e.g., `discount_code_basic`, `discount_code_app`).

source_relation.name: source_relation
source_relation.description: The schema or database this record came from if you are making use of the `shopify_union_schemas` or `shopify_union_databases` variables, respectively. Empty string if you are not using either of these variables to union together multiple Shopify connectors.

source.shopify_source.shopify.collection.name: collection
source.shopify_source.shopify.collection.description: A collection is a grouping of products that merchants can create to make their stores easier to browse. Merchants can create collections by selecting products individually or by defining rules that automatically determine whether products are included (aka a "smart collection").

_fivetran_deleted.name: _fivetran_deleted
_fivetran_deleted.description: Boolean representing whether the record was soft-deleted in Shopify.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced

disjunctive.name: disjunctive
disjunctive.description: Boolean representing whether the `rules` or disjuctive (logical `OR`) or not. True = disjuctive, false = conjunctive (logical `AND`).

handle.name: handle
handle.description: A unique, human-readable string for the collection automatically generated from its title. This is used in themes by the Liquid templating language to refer to the collection.

id.name: id
id.description: The ID for the collection.

published_at.name: published_at
published_at.description: The time and date (ISO 8601 format) when the collection was made visible. Returns null for a hidden collection.

published_scope.name: published_scope
published_scope.description: Whether the collection is published to the Point of Sale channel. Valid values `web` (the collection is published to the Online Store channel but not published to the Point of Sale channel) and `global` (the collection is published to both the Online Store channel and the Point of Sale channel).

rules.name: rules
rules.description: An array of rules that define what products go into the smart collection. Each rule (`column` -- `relation` --> `condition`) has these properties: - `column`: the property of a product being used to populate the smart collection. Ex: 'tag', 'type', 'vendor', 'variant_price', etc. - `relation`: The comparitive relationship between the column choice, and the condition ('equals', 'contains', 'greater_than', etc.) - condition: Select products for a smart collection using a condition. Values are either strings or numbers, depending on the relation value. See the [Shopify docs](https://shopify.dev/api/admin-rest/2022-10/resources/smartcollection#resource-object) for more.

sort_order.name: sort_order
sort_order.description: The order of the products in the collection. Valid values inclide - `alpha-asc`: The products are sorted alphabetically from A to Z. - `alpha-des`: The products are sorted alphabetically from Z to A. - `best-selling`: The products are sorted by number of sales. - `created`: The products are sorted by the date they were created, from oldest to newest. - `created-desc`: The products are sorted by the date they were created, from newest to oldest. - `manual`: The products are manually sorted by the shop owner. - `price-asc`: The products are sorted by price from lowest to highest. - `price-desc`: The products are sorted by price from highest to lowest.

title.name: title
title.description: The name of the collection

updated_at.name: updated_at
updated_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the collection was last modified.

source.shopify_source.shopify.fulfillmen.name: fulfillment
source.shopify_source.shopify.fulfillmen.description: A fulfillment order represents a group of one or more items in an order that will be fulfilled from the same location.  A fulfillment represents work that is completed as part of a fulfillment order and can include one or more items.

created_at.description: The date and time when the fulfillment was created. The API returns this value in ISO 8601 format.

id.name: id
id.description: The ID for the fulfillment.

location_id.name: location_id
location_id.description: The unique identifier of the location that the fulfillment was processed at.

name.name: name
name.description: The uniquely identifying fulfillment name, consisting of two parts separated by a .. The first part represents the order name and the second part represents the fulfillment number.  The fulfillment number automatically increments depending on how many fulfillments are in an order (e.g. #1001.1, #1001.2).

order_id.name: order_id

service.description: The fulfillment service associated with the fulfillment.

shipment_status.name: shipment_status
shipment_status.description: The current shipment status of the fulfillment. Valid values include: - label_printed: A label for the shipment was purchased and printed. - label_purchased: A label for the shipment was purchased, but not printed. - attempted_delivery: Delivery of the shipment was attempted, but unable to be completed. - ready_for_pickup: The shipment is ready for pickup at a shipping depot. - confirmed: The carrier is aware of the shipment, but hasn't received it yet. - in_transit: The shipment is being transported between shipping facilities on the way to its destination. - out_for_delivery: The shipment is being delivered to its final destination. - delivered: The shipment was succesfully delivered. - failure: Something went wrong when pulling tracking information for the shipment, such as the tracking number was invalid or the shipment was canceled.

status.name: status
status.description: The status of the fulfillment. Valid values include: - pending: Shopify has created the fulfillment and is waiting for the third-party fulfillment service to transition it to 'open' or 'success'. - open: The fulfillment has been acknowledged by the service and is in processing. - success: The fulfillment was successful. - cancelled: The fulfillment was cancelled. - error: There was an error with the fulfillment request. - failure: The fulfillment request failed.

source.shopify_source.shopify.fulfillmen.description: The FulfillmentEvent resource represents tracking events that belong to a fulfillment of one or more items in an order.  Fulfillment events are displayed on the order status page to update customers on the status of their shipment.

_fivetran_deleted.description: Boolean representing whether the record was soft-deleted in Shopify.

_fivetran_synced.description: The time when a record was last updated by Fivetran.

address_1.description: The street address where the fulfillment event occurred.

city.name: city
city.description: The city where the fulfillment event occurred.

country.name: country
country.description: The country where the fulfillment event occurred.

created_at.name: created_at
created_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the fulfillment event was created.

estimated_delivery_at.name: estimated_delivery_at
estimated_delivery_at.description: The estimated delivery date based on the fulfillment's tracking number, as long as it's provided by one of the following carriers: USPS, FedEx, UPS, or Canada Post (Canada only).  Value is `null` if no tracking number is available or if the tracking number is from an unsupported carrier. This property is available only when carrier calculated rates are in use.

fulfillment_id.name: fulfillment_id
fulfillment_id.description: An ID for the fulfillment that's associated with the fulfillment event.

happened_at.name: happened_at
happened_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the fulfillment event occurred.

id.name: id
id.description: An ID for the fulfillment event.

latitude.name: latitude
latitude.description: A geographic coordinate specifying the latitude of the fulfillment event.

longitude.name: longitude
longitude.description: A geographic coordinate specifying the longitude of the fulfillment event.

message.name: message
message.description: An arbitrary message describing the status. Can be provided by a shipping carrier.

order_id.name: order_id
order_id.description: The ID of the order that's associated with the fulfillment event.

province.name: province
province.description: The province where the fulfillment event occurred.

shop_id.name: shop_id
shop_id.description: An ID for the shop that's associated with the fulfillment event.

status.name: status
status.description: The status of the fulfillment event. Valid values: - label_printed: A label for the shipment was purchased and printed. - label_purchased: A label for the shipment was purchased, but not printed. - attempted_delivery: Delivery of the shipment was attempted, but unable to be completed. - ready_for_pickup: The shipment is ready for pickup at a shipping depot. - picked_up: The fulfillment was successfully picked up. - confirmed: The carrier is aware of the shipment, but hasn't received it yet. - in_transit: The shipment is being transported between shipping facilities on the way to its destination. - out_for_delivery: The shipment is being delivered to its final destination. - delivered: The shipment was successfully delivered. - failure: Something went wrong when pulling tracking information for the shipment, such as the tracking number was invalid or the shipment was canceled.

updated_at.name: updated_at
updated_at.description: The date and time (ISO 8601 format) when the fulfillment event was updated.

zip.name: zip
zip.description: The zip code of the location where the fulfillment event occurred.

sort_order.description: The order of the products in the collection. Valid values inclide - `alpha-asc`: The products are sorted alphabetically from A to Z. - `alpha-des`: The products are sorted alphabetically from Z to A. - `best-selling`: The products are sorted by number of sales. - `created`: The products are sorted by the date they were created, from oldest to newest. - `created-desc`: The products are sorted by the date they were created, from newest to oldest. - `manual`: The products are manually sorted by the shop owner. - `price-asc`: The products are sorted by price from lowest to highest. - `price-desc`: The products are sorted by price from highest to lowest.

Valid values: - label_printed: A label for the shipment was purchased and printed. - label_purchased: A label for the shipment was purchased, but not printed. - attempted_delivery: Delivery of the shipment was attempted, but unable to be completed. - ready_for_pickup: The shipment is ready for pickup at a shipping depot. - confirmed: The carrier is aware of the shipment, but hasn't received it yet. - in_transit: The shipment is being transported between shipping facilities on the way to its destination. - out_for_delivery: The shipment is being delivered to its final destination. - delayed: The shipment was delayed.   - delivered: The shipment was successfully delivered. - failure: Something went wrong when pulling tracking information for the shipment, such as the tracking number was invalid or the shipment was canceled.

macro.dbt_postgres.postgres__get_relatio.name: postgres__get_relations
macro.dbt_postgres.postgres__get_relatio.macro_sql:
{% macro postgres__get_relations() -%}

  {#
      -- in pg_depend, objid is the dependent, refobjid is the referenced object
      --  > a pg_depend entry indicates that the referenced object cannot be
      --  > dropped without also dropping the dependent object.
  #}

  {%- call statement('relations', fetch_result=True) -%}
    with relation as (
        select
            pg_rewrite.ev_class as class,
            pg_rewrite.oid as id
        from pg_rewrite
    ),
    class as (
        select
            oid as id,
            relname as name,
            relnamespace as schema,
            relkind as kind
        from pg_class
    ),
    dependency as (
        select distinct
            pg_depend.objid as id,
            pg_depend.refobjid as ref
        from pg_depend
    ),
    schema as (
        select
            pg_namespace.oid as id,
            pg_namespace.nspname as name
        from pg_namespace
        where nspname != 'information_schema' and nspname not like 'pg\_%'
    ),
    referenced as (
        select
            relation.id AS id,
            referenced_class.name ,
            referenced_class.schema ,
            referenced_class.kind
        from relation
        join class as referenced_class on relation.class=referenced_class.id
        where referenced_class.kind in ('r', 'v', 'm')
    ),
    relationships as (
        select
            referenced.name as referenced_name,
            referenced.schema as referenced_schema_id,
            dependent_class.name as dependent_name,
            dependent_class.schema as dependent_schema_id,
            referenced.kind as kind
        from referenced
        join dependency on referenced.id=dependency.id
        join class as dependent_class on dependency.ref=dependent_class.id
        where
            (referenced.name != dependent_class.name or
             referenced.schema != dependent_class.schema)
    )

    select
        referenced_schema.name as referenced_schema,
        relationships.referenced_name as referenced_name,
        dependent_schema.name as dependent_schema,
        relationships.dependent_name as dependent_name
    from relationships
    join schema as dependent_schema on relationships.dependent_schema_id=dependent_schema.id
    join schema as referenced_schema on relationships.referenced_schema_id=referenced_schema.id
    group by referenced_schema, referenced_name, dependent_schema, dependent_name
    order by referenced_schema, referenced_name, dependent_schema, dependent_name;

  {%- endcall -%}

  {{ return(load_result('relations').table) }}
{% endmacro %}

macro.dbt_postgres.postgres__list_relati.name: postgres__list_relations_without_caching
macro.dbt_postgres.postgres__list_relati.macro_sql:
{% macro postgres__list_relations_without_caching(schema_relation) %}
  {% call statement('list_relations_without_caching', fetch_result=True) -%}
    select
      '{{ schema_relation.database }}' as database,
      tablename as name,
      schemaname as schema,
      'table' as type
    from pg_tables
    where schemaname ilike '{{ schema_relation.schema }}'
    union all
    select
      '{{ schema_relation.database }}' as database,
      viewname as name,
      schemaname as schema,
      'view' as type
    from pg_views
    where schemaname ilike '{{ schema_relation.schema }}'
    union all
    select
      '{{ schema_relation.database }}' as database,
      matviewname as name,
      schemaname as schema,
      'materialized_view' as type
    from pg_matviews
    where schemaname ilike '{{ schema_relation.schema }}'
  {% endcall %}
  {{ return(load_result('list_relations_without_caching').table) }}
{% endmacro %}

macro.dbt_postgres.postgres__get_show_in.name: postgres__get_show_indexes_sql
macro.dbt_postgres.postgres__get_show_in.macro_sql:
{% macro postgres__get_show_indexes_sql(relation) %}
    select
        i.relname                                   as name,
        m.amname                                    as method,
        ix.indisunique                              as "unique",
        array_to_string(array_agg(a.attname), ',')  as column_names
    from pg_index ix
    join pg_class i
        on i.oid = ix.indexrelid
    join pg_am m
        on m.oid=i.relam
    join pg_class t
        on t.oid = ix.indrelid
    join pg_namespace n
        on n.oid = t.relnamespace
    join pg_attribute a
        on a.attrelid = t.oid
        and a.attnum = ANY(ix.indkey)
    where t.relname = '{{ relation.identifier }}'
      and n.nspname = '{{ relation.schema }}'
      and t.relkind in ('r', 'm')
    group by 1, 2, 3
    order by 1, 2, 3
{% endmacro %}

doc.dbt.__overview__.name: __overview__
doc.dbt.__overview__.block_contents:
### Welcome!

Welcome to the auto-generated documentation for your dbt project!

### Navigation

You can use the `Project` and `Database` navigation tabs on the left side of the window to explore the models
in your project.

#### Project Tab
The `Project` tab mirrors the directory structure of your dbt project. In this tab, you can see all of the
models defined in your dbt project, as well as models imported from dbt packages.

#### Database Tab
The `Database` tab also exposes your models, but in a format that looks more like a database explorer. This view
shows relations (tables and views) grouped into database schemas. Note that ephemeral models are _not_ shown
in this interface, as they do not exist in the database.

### Graph Exploration
You can click the blue icon on the bottom-right corner of the page to view the lineage graph of your models.

On model pages, you'll see the immediate parents and children of the model you're exploring. By clicking the `Expand`
button at the top-right of this lineage pane, you'll be able to see all of the models that are used to build,
or are built from, the model you're exploring.

Once expanded, you'll be able to use the `--select` and `--exclude` model selection syntax to filter the
models in the graph. For more information on model selection, check out the [dbt docs](https://docs.getdbt.com/docs/model-selection-syntax).

Note that you can also right-click on models to interactively filter and explore the graph.

---

### More information

- [What is dbt](https://docs.getdbt.com/docs/introduction)?
- Read the [dbt viewpoint](https://docs.getdbt.com/docs/viewpoint)
- [Installation](https://docs.getdbt.com/docs/installation)
- Join the [dbt Community](https://www.getdbt.com/community/) for questions and discussion

model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__co.name: stg_shopify_gql__collection_rule
model.shopify_source.stg_shopify_gql__co.description: Defines the rules used to automatically include products in a smart collection. Each rule specifies a product attribute, a comparison relation, and a condition value to match against. These rules are evaluated dynamically to determine collection membership without manual curation.

_fivetran_synced.name: _fivetran_synced
_fivetran_synced.description: {{ doc('_fivetran_synced') }}

collection_id.name: collection_id
collection_id.description: The ID of the smart collection to which this rule applies.

index.name: index
index.description: The position of the rule within the collection's rule set.  Rules are evaluated in order and may be grouped depending on collection logic.

condition.name: condition
condition.description: The value to compare against the attribute. For example, “Hats” if the rule is targeting products with a title containing “Hats”. The interpretation depends on the associated `relation` and `columns` values.

relation.name: relation
relation.description: The operator used to evaluate the rule. Common values include: - `equals` - `contains` - `not_equals` - `starts_with` - `ends_with` - `is_set` - `is_not_set` - `greater_than` - `less_than` - `not_contains`

columns.name: columns
columns.description: The attribute being evaluated by the rule. Example values include: - `title` - `vendor` - `tag` - `variant_price` - `product_category_id` - `variant_compare_at_price` - `variant_metafield_definition` - `product_metafield_definition` - `variant_weight` - `type` - `is_price_reduced`
